# JetBrains IDE Configuration Standards

Apply these conventions when creating or modifying JetBrains IDE configuration files (IntelliJ IDEA, WebStorm, GoLand, PyCharm, Rider).

## What to Commit

Commit shared project configuration under `.idea/`. Exclude personal settings:

**Commit these files:**

- `.idea/codeStyles/` — shared code style settings
- `.idea/inspectionProfiles/` — shared inspection profiles
- `.idea/runConfigurations/` — shared run/debug configurations
- `.idea/vcs.xml` — VCS integration settings
- `.idea/externalDependencies.xml` — required plugins list
- `.idea/*.iml` module files (for non-Gradle/Maven projects)

**Add to `.gitignore`:**

```gitignore
.idea/workspace.xml
.idea/tasks.xml
.idea/usage.statistics.xml
.idea/dictionaries/
.idea/shelf/
.idea/httpRequests/
.idea/.name
*.iws
```

## Code Style Settings

Define project-level code style in `.idea/codeStyles/Project.xml`. Set the formatter to follow language-standard conventions:

- **Go**: `gofmt` / `goimports` defaults — no custom overrides needed
- **Python**: PEP 8 with 4-space indentation, 120-character line length
- **TypeScript/JavaScript**: Prettier-compatible formatting — 2-space indentation, single quotes, trailing commas
- **Java/Kotlin**: Google Java Style or Kotlin Coding Conventions

Enable "Reformat code on save" in the project code style settings to match `editor.formatOnSave` in VS Code.

## Run Configurations

Store shared run configurations in `.idea/runConfigurations/` using descriptive XML filenames:

```xml
<!-- .idea/runConfigurations/Run_Server.xml -->
<component name="ProjectRunConfigurationManager">
  <configuration default="false" name="Run Server" type="GoApplicationRunConfiguration" factoryName="Go Application">
    <module name="myproject" />
    <working_directory value="$PROJECT_DIR$" />
    <kind value="DIRECTORY" />
    <directory value="$PROJECT_DIR$/cmd/server" />
    <envs>
      <env name="ENV" value="development" />
    </envs>
  </configuration>
</component>
```

Provide configurations for:

- Main application entry point
- Test suite (all tests)
- Linter / code quality check

## Inspection Profiles

Use a project-level inspection profile rather than the IDE default. Store in `.idea/inspectionProfiles/Project_Default.xml`. Disable noisy or irrelevant inspections per project — keep the signal-to-noise ratio high.

## External Dependencies (Required Plugins)

List plugins the team needs in `.idea/externalDependencies.xml`:

```xml
<project version="4">
  <component name="ExternalDependencies">
    <plugin id="org.jetbrains.plugins.go" />
    <plugin id="HashiCorp.HCLLanguageSupport" />
  </component>
</project>
```

JetBrains IDEs prompt teammates to install missing plugins on project open.

## Database and HTTP Client

Store shared database connection configs in `.idea/dataSources.xml` (without credentials). Use the built-in HTTP client with `.http` files under a `http/` directory for API testing — these are version-controllable alternatives to Postman collections.
